{% if extraction_target == "entities" %}
Extract entities from the corroboration document page, following the ontology exactly.

ENTITY ONTOLOGY:
{% for e in entity_ontology_rich %}
  Type        : {{ e.type }}
  Description : {{ e.description }}
  Next ID     : {{ e.next_id }}  ← use this for the first new {{ e.type }}, then increment
  label       : write a short human-readable summary of this entity (e.g. "John Smith", "Alpine Bank savings account", "CHF 50k transfer to GlobalTech")
  Attributes  : {{ e.attributes | tojson }}
{% endfor %}

ENTITIES ALREADY IN THE GRAPH — do NOT create new nodes for these; use their existing IDs:
{{ known_entities | tojson(indent=2) }}

MATCHING RULE: Before extracting a new entity, check if any entity in the list above
matches by name, alias, or description. If it matches — even partially or under a
slightly different spelling — use the existing entity's ID in the relationship step
instead of creating a new node.

DOCUMENT SUMMARY:
{{ document_summary }}

PAGE {{ page_number }} SUMMARY:
{{ page_summary }}

Return ONLY entities NOT already in the graph above:

{
  "entities": [
    {
      "id": "<next_id for this type — must not clash with any existing ID above>",
      "type": "<entity type from ontology>",
      "label": "<concise human-readable description of this entity>",
      "attributes": {
        "<every attribute for this type>": "<value or null>"
      }
    }
  ],
  "entities_to_remove": []
}

Rules:
- Use ONLY ontology-defined types and attributes.
- "label" must be a concise human-readable description of the entity. Do NOT copy an attribute value verbatim.
- Every attribute must appear — use null if not found.
- Do not invent values.

{% else %}
Extract relationships from the corroboration document page, following the ontology exactly.

RELATIONSHIP ONTOLOGY — for each type the exact attributes to include are listed:
{% for r in relationship_ontology_rich %}
  Type       : {{ r.type }}
  Description: {{ r.description }}
  From       : {{ r.from | join(" or ") }}  →  To: {{ r.to | join(" or ") }}
  Attributes : {{ r.attributes | tojson }}
  Required output structure for this type:
    {
      "type": "{{ r.type }}",
      "source": "<id of a {{ r.from | join(' or ') }} entity>",
      "target": "<id of a {{ r.to | join(' or ') }} entity>",
      "attributes": {
        "evidence": "<verbatim or paraphrased quote from document>",
        {% if r.attributes is mapping %}{% for attr in r.attributes.keys() %}"{{ attr }}": "<value or null>"{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
        {% endfor %}{% endif %}
      }
    }
{% endfor %}

ALL AVAILABLE ENTITIES (use their exact IDs as source/target):
{{ known_entities | tojson(indent=2) }}

DOCUMENT SUMMARY:
{{ document_summary }}

PAGE {{ page_number }} SUMMARY:
{{ page_summary }}

Return:
{
  "relationships": [ ... one object per relationship, using the structure shown above for each type ... ],
  "relationships_to_remove": []
}

Rules:
- Use ONLY relationship types defined in the ontology above.
- source/target must match the allowed From/To entity types for each relationship.
- Include ONLY the attribute keys shown for the specific relationship type plus "evidence". Do NOT add any other keys.
- Every listed attribute must appear in the output — use null if the value is not found in the document.
- "evidence" is REQUIRED on every relationship — never leave it empty or null.
- Do NOT include a "reasoning" field.
- You may link history KG entities to new corroboration entities.
{% endif %}
